item.title: CVE-2017-2886|2024-08-05T14:09:17.754Z -- acdsee -- acdsee%20ultimate
item.description: A memory corruption vulnerability exists in the .PSD parsing functionality of ACDSee Ultimate 10.0.0.292. A specially crafted .PSD file can cause an out of bounds write vulnerability resulting in potential code execution. An attacker can send a specific .PSD file to trigger this vulnerability.
